        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Check ClawHub trust before plugin and skill installs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nOpenClaw now checks ClawHub exact-release trust before downloading ClawHub plugin releases and archive-backed ClawHub skill releases. Malicious or ClawHub-blocked releases fail closed before download; suspicious or failed-review releases require an interactive acknowledgement or `--acknowledge-clawhub-risk`; pending or stale non-risk trust states warn without blocking.\n\nOfficial/source-linked ClawHub metadata remains a trust signal in package records and UI, but it is not a bypass for the release security gate. For example, `@openclaw/kitchen-sink` is treated as an official/source-linked plugin when ClawHub reports that metadata, but install policy still follows the exact release trust response.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Shared ClawHub release trust gate: plugin installs and skill archive installs now use the same disposition model for clean, review-recommended, review-required, blocked, stale, and unavailable trust data.\n- Plugin installs and updates: preserve the existing plugin behavior from the original trust PR, including typed acknowledgement for risky releases and install-record trust metadata.\n- Skill installs and updates: ClawHub archive-backed skills check the selected `slug@version` verdict before archive download; owner-qualified skills validate the returned publisher and show `@owner/slug` in warnings and typed acknowledgements.\n- Skill CLI: `openclaw skills install` and `openclaw skills update` now accept `--acknowledge-clawhub-risk` for reviewed non-interactive automation.\n- GitHub-backed ClawHub skills: continue to use the ClawHub install resolver as the policy boundary because the skill security-verdict API is version-based, not commit-resolution based.\n- Docs: ClawHub and skills CLI docs now describe the trust gate and acknowledgement flag for both plugins and skills.\n\n## Proof\n\nReviewer-checkable behavior from the local ClawHub fixture command transcript:\n\n| Scenario | Command Surface | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| malicious / blocked plugin release | `openclaw plugins install clawhub:<package>` | exits `1`, prints `BLOCKED`, does not install |\n| suspicious plugin release without acknowledgement | `openclaw plugins install clawhub:<package>` | exits `1`, prints `REVIEW REQUIRED` |\n| suspicious plugin release with acknowledgement | `openclaw plugins install clawhub:<package> --acknowledge-clawhub-risk` | exits `0`, warning remains visible |\n| clean community plugin release | `openclaw plugins install clawhub:<package>` | exits `0` |\n| clean official/source-linked plugin release | `openclaw plugins install clawhub:<package>` | exits `0` |\n| malicious / blocked skill release | `openclaw skills install @owner/<slug> --global` | exits `1`, prints `BLOCKED`, does not install |\n| suspicious skill release without acknowledgement | `openclaw skills install @owner/<slug> --global` | exits `1`, prints `REVIEW REQUIRED` |\n| suspicious skill release with acknowledgement | `openclaw skills install @owner/<slug> --global --acknowledge-clawhub-risk` | exits `0`, warning remains visible |\n| clean community skill release | `openclaw skills install @owner/<slug> --global` | exits `0` |\n| clean official/source-linked skill release | `openclaw skills install @owner/<slug> --global` | exits `0` |\n\nThe skill transcript also verifies owner-qualified warning links like `/community/kitchen-sink`, so risky owner-qualified releases are not acknowledged as a bare slug.\n\nScreenshots: not included. This PR changes CLI, install policy, docs, and tests; there is no changed human-visible web UI state where a screenshot would prove more than the command matrix.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal checks run after the skill extension:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts src/cli/skills-cli.commands.test.ts src/plugins/clawhub.test.ts src/cli/clawhub-risk-acknowledgement.test.ts` passed: 3 shards, 189 tests.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/update-cli.test.ts src/cli/update-cli/update-command.test.ts src/cli/update-cli/post-core-plugin-convergence.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/skills.clawhub.test.ts src/infra/clawhub.test.ts` passed: 3 shards, 296 tests.\n- `node .artifacts/clawhub-install-trust/run-proof.cjs` passed and regenerated the local command transcript for the ten plugin/skill trust scenarios above.\n- `pnpm docs:list` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `rg -n \"^(<<<<<<<|=======|>>>>>>>)\" src docs .artifacts/clawhub-install-trust/run-proof.cjs .artifacts/clawhub-install-trust/install-command-output.md` returned no matches.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` passed with no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nNot run locally after the skill extension: full `pnpm check` / full build. Those are left to CI because the local proof is focused on the touched install, CLI, docs, and ClawHub trust surfaces.\n",
        "branch": "jesse/clawhub-install-trust-remake",
